The paper deals with the study of polyhedra and their graphs, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of clustered planarity, which is used to recognize the graphs of 4-treetopes, is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves the study of graph theory (cs.GT) and algorithms (cs.DS) for recognizing certain types of graphs. Finally, the use of polynomial time algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.SI).
